accomodations.Address: 1899 Jongdal-ri, Gujwa-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
accomodations.Description:
The 제주도 레인보우 펜션 is a 5-star accommodation located in Gujwa-eup, Jeju-do, South Korea, offering an ideal stay for families, couples, and business travelers alike. Nestled in the heart of Jeju Island, the 펜션 boasts a prime location near key landmarks and attractions, including the Jeju International Airport, which is just a short drive away.

The 제주도 레인보우 펜션 features comfortable and clean rooms, each equipped with modern amenities to ensure a pleasant stay. Guests can enjoy a variety of room types, including standard rooms, suites, and family rooms, all designed with the utmost comfort and convenience in mind.

In addition to its comfortable accommodations, the 펜션 offers a range of on-site facilities and services, including a restaurant serving delicious local cuisine, a fitness center, and a business center for those traveling on business. The 펜션's proximity to popular tourist destinations, such as the Seongsan Ilchulbong and the Jeju Folk Village, makes it an ideal base for exploring the island.

Guests of the 제주도 레인보우 펜션 can expect exceptional service and attention to detail, as evidenced by its 5/5 overall rating. With its combination of comfort, convenience, and affordability, the 펜션 is an excellent choice for those looking for a memorable stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: 제주도 레인보우 펜션

accomodations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 대한민국 제주특별자치도 제주시 구좌읍 평대리 3200-5
accomodations.Description: 비자숲길15는 대한민국 제주특별자치도 제주시 구좌읍 평대리 3200-5에 위치한 4.6/5 평점의 호텔입니다. 이 호텔은 가족, 커플, 비즈니스 여행객 모두에게 이상적인 선택입니다. 호텔은 편안한 객실과 다양한 편의 시설을 제공하며, 손님들은 청결하고 편안한 숙박을 즐길 수 있습니다. 비자숲길15는 주변 관광지와 교통편과의 접근성이 좋아, 제주도를 탐험하기에 최적의 위치를 자랑합니다. 호텔은 맛있는 음식과 훌륭한 서비스를 제공하여 손님들에게 특별한 경험을 선사합니다. 전반적으로, 비자숲길15는 편안하고 편리한 숙박을 원하는 분들에게 추천할 만한 호텔입니다.
accomodations.Name: 비자숲길15

accomodations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 1966-34 sanroknamro,seoquiposi, Halla Mountain National Park
accomodations.Description: Ive Resort Jeju agoda is a 4.2/5-rated hotel located in South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 1966-34 sanroknamro,seoquiposi, Halla Mountain National Park. The hotel is ideal for families and couples seeking a peaceful retreat, as it offers a great location close to Hanla mountain. The resort features comfortable and clean rooms, friendly and helpful staff, and excellent service. Guests can enjoy the value for money offered by the resort, with amenities such as dining options and room types catering to various preferences. While the hotel is a little farther away from the main town, it provides a perfect escape for those looking to relax and enjoy the natural beauty of the area.
accomodations.Name: Ive Resort Jeju agoda

accomodations.Address: South Korea, Cheju, 한림읍 화전길 82 제주시 KR
accomodations.Description: Ardenhill Resort is a 4.1/5-rated hotel located in South Korea, Cheju, at 한림읍 화전길 82. This resort stands out for its pet-friendly policy, allowing guests to bring their furry friends along. While some reviewers have noted that the pet-allowed rooms can have a slight odor, the overall guest experience is positive. The resort offers comfortable and clean accommodations, with a range of room types and amenities to cater to various traveler needs. Its proximity to key landmarks and attractions in Jeju Island makes it an ideal choice for families, couples, and business travelers alike. With its unique features and focus on guest satisfaction, Ardenhill Resort is a great option for those seeking a memorable stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: Ardenhill Resort

accomodations.Address: 75-9 Sanbang-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
accomodations.Description: Ocean Brick is a 3.8/5-rated hotel located in Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea. It offers spacious villas with cozy bedrooms, small kitchens, and a main swimming pool with heating. The hotel is ideal for families and couples looking for a quiet getaway, but it's important to note that there are a lot of mosquitoes and no cleaning service. The location is a bit far from popular attractions, so guests may need to travel by car. The closest beach is not suitable for swimming due to trash, but there are nearby grottoes and Yeongmeori coast. The hotel does not offer breakfast or have a cafe, and the pool at the villa requires an additional fee for usage. Despite the low room fee, guests should not expect exceptional service.
accomodations.Name: Ocean Brick

accomodations.Address: 303 Dochidol-gil, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
accomodations.Description: The Log Park Hotel, located in Jeju Island, is a 4.2/5-rated accommodation that offers a unique experience for families and couples. Nestled in a picturesque setting, the hotel features a ranch where guests can interact with alpacas and purchase alpaca-related products. The log houses are well-equipped and spacious, providing a cozy and rustic feel. The hotel is known for its excellent service, cleanliness, and comfortable heating system. Guests can enjoy the surrounding nature, with opportunities to stroll around and see horses. The hotel is a great choice for those looking to unwind and enjoy the countryside, with a campfire and BBQ facilities available. The Log Park Hotel is an ideal destination for families and couples seeking a peaceful and memorable stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: Log Park Hotel

accomodations.Description: Staz Hotel Jeju Robero is a 3.9/5-rated hotel located at 26 Gwandeok-ro, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea. The hotel offers bright and relaxed rooms with a restaurant, lounge, and sauna, along with free parking. It is ideal for families, couples, and business travelers. The hotel's location is decent, not too far from the open-air market but still a bit of a walk from the waterfront. The staff is helpful and kind, and the location is convenient for visiting key landmarks and attractions, such as the Jeju central Catholic church. The rooms are spacious and fair for the price, with notable features including a comfortable bed, shower gel, soap, shampoo, and mineral water. The hotel also offers storage for luggage at the lobby. Overall, Staz Hotel Jeju Robero provides good value for money and is a great choice for travelers looking for a comfortable and convenient stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: Staz Hotel Jeju Robero

data.description: Embark on a thrilling 7-Day Jeju Island Adventure, starting December 1st, 2024, where you'll explore the island's breathtaking natural wonders and cultural gems. Visit iconic sites like Seongsan Ilchulbong, Manjanggul Lava Tube, and Hallasan National Park, including the Witseoreum Volcanic Cone and Si Oreum. Immerse yourself in the island's rich culture at Hallim Park, Jeju Folklore and Natural History Museum, and the picturesque Sanyang Keunkot Photo Spot. Enjoy the stunning coastal views at Yongmeori Coast and Yongduam Rock, and have fun at Soingook Theme Park. Don't miss the unique experiences at Jimibong, Geomun Oreum, and Dodubong Peak. This unforgettable journey ends on December 7th, 2024."

destinations.Address: 78 Seongsan-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Seongsan Ilchulbong, a renowned volcanic cone in Jeju Island, is a must-visit natural landmark with a bowl-shaped crater and a popular hiking route. Located in Seongsan-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, this attraction boasts an overall rating of 4.6/5 and is ideal for families, adventurers, and nature lovers. Visitors can expect stunning views, a paid entry, and a unique hiking experience with well-maintained paths and resting spots. The summit offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding landscape, making it a perfect spot for photography enthusiasts. Additionally, there are free areas with great views towards the summit and a tiny temple. For Korean visitors, there are culture and nature guides available on the top who can provide interesting information about the summit, Jeju culture, nature, and amazing stories. Seongsan Ilchulbong is easily accessible and close to other popular places in Jeju Island, making it a perfect addition to any travel itinerary.
destinations.Name: Seongsan Ilchulbong

destinations.Address: 182 Manjanggul-gil, Gujwa-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description:
Manjanggul Lava Tube is a natural landmark located in Jeju Island, South Korea, known for its unique lava tube formations and diverse igneous rock formations. With a 4.2/5 overall rating, visitors can expect a memorable experience, immersing themselves in the wonder of nature. The attraction is ideal for families, nature lovers, and adventure seekers, offering a 1km-long trail that takes approximately 1 hour to complete. The lava tube features unique stalactites and stalagmites, as well as a variety of bats and insects.

In addition to the lava tube, visitors can learn about the history of the site at the indoor information center and enjoy local cuisine at the nearby restaurant, which offers fried cheese pork cutlet and udon. The ticket price is 4,000 won per adult, and there is plenty of outdoor parking space available.

Visitors should note that the floor of the lava tube is rough and uneven, making walking challenging for some. It is recommended to wear suitable shoes for walking and to be prepared for a cooler temperature inside the cave. The lava tube is a must-see attraction in Jeju Island, with its stunning beauty and unique geological features.
destinations.Name: Manjanggul Lava Tube

destinations.Address: South Korea, 제주특별자치도 제주시 조천읍 선흘리
destinations.Description: Geomun Oreum, a self-guided and assisted tour attraction, is an ancient volcanic crater located in Jeju Island, South Korea. With a 4.6/5 overall rating, visitors can expect a unique experience as they explore the crater's trees, caves, and scenic views. As a UNESCO natural heritage site, Geomun Oreum is a must-visit for nature lovers and history enthusiasts. The attraction offers three different trails, ranging from 1-3 hours in length, providing a variety of experiences for visitors. While some reviewers found the entrance fee to be pricey, many praised the peaceful atmosphere and the opportunity to learn about the site's significance as the "mother of Jeju" from knowledgeable tour guides. With its beautiful scenery and healing environment, Geomun Oreum is an ideal destination for those seeking a memorable and educational experience in Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Geomun Oreum

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, Gujwa-eup, Jongdal-ri, 266 제주특별자치도
destinations.Description: Jimibong, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated natural landmark that offers visitors a low-key hiking experience with stunning views. With an overall rating of 4.6/5, this attraction is ideal for nature lovers and families seeking a scenic adventure. The hike to the top takes approximately 15 minutes and is well-maintained, making it accessible for beginners. Visitors can expect breathtaking panoramic views from the summit, which is a popular spot for photography. The location of Jimibong is conveniently close to other key landmarks in Jeju Island, making it a perfect addition to any travel itinerary. Visitor reviews highlight the beauty and accessibility of the hike, with many describing the view from the top as "amazing" and "one of the best views ever."
destinations.Name: Jimibong

destinations.Description: Hallasan National Park, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a must-visit destination for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. With a 4.7/5 overall rating, this national park is renowned for its large mountain, featuring a variety of alpine plants and offering breathtaking views. Visitors can expect a challenging hike with steep stairs and a fair mix of rocks, making it ideal for those seeking an adrenaline rush. The park is also home to diverse wildlife, providing opportunities for wildlife encounters. With two restrooms and no water available, it's essential to plan your visit accordingly. The park's location near Jeju Island's key landmarks makes it easily accessible for tourists. Visitor experiences highlight the park's beauty, accessibility, and the rewarding path to the summit, where you can enjoy panoramic views of the island.
destinations.Name: Hallasan National Park

destinations.Description:
Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain, located in Seoho-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea, is a natural landmark that offers visitors a unique and memorable experience. With a perfect 5/5 overall rating, this attraction is ideal for nature lovers and adventurers seeking scenic views and a chance to explore the island's geological history.

Visitors can expect to find a stunning volcanic cone formation, which is a rare and beautiful sight. The location of Witseoreum Volcanic Cone is convenient, as it is close to other popular landmarks in Jeju Island, making it easy to include in a larger itinerary.

Reviews from visitors highlight the beauty and accessibility of the attraction, with many praising the stunning views and the opportunity to learn about the island's volcanic history. The unique and rare wildlife found in the area is also a notable special feature, making Witseoreum Volcanic Cone a must-visit for nature enthusiasts and photographers.

In summary, Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain is a natural landmark that offers visitors a chance to explore the island's geological history, enjoy stunning views, and encounter rare wildlife. Its ideal location and perfect overall rating make it a top choice for nature lovers and adventurers visiting Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain

destinations.Description:
Si Oreum is a natural landmark located in Hogeun-dong, Jeju-si, South Korea, and is part of a UNESCO park. Visitors can expect a stunning natural formation that is a result of a volcanic eruption. The attraction is ideal for families, adventurers, and nature lovers who appreciate the beauty and uniqueness of the island's geological features. The location is easily accessible from the central volcano and the surrounding countryside, making it a convenient stop for tourists.

The underground tube at Si Oreum plunges visitors into the Earth, offering a unique and unforgettable experience. The flat, wet, and cold surface of black basalt, combined with the spectral artificial lights, creates a mesmerizing atmosphere. Visitors can explore the pools of water gathered in the wrinkles of the hardened lava floor, making it a must-visit for those seeking a memorable experience.

With an overall rating of 4.6/5 and positive reviews from visitors, Si Oreum is a highly recommended attraction for those visiting Jeju Island. Visitors can expect a cheap ticket price and a chance to descend through a prehistoric tube into the Earth, making it a one-of-a-kind experience.
destinations.Name: Si Oreum

destinations.Address: 300 Hallim-ro, Hallim-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Hallim Park, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated tourist attraction with a 4.4/5 overall rating. Visitors can expect a variety of scenic gardens, two caves, and a small zoo, as well as a folk village. The park is ideal for families, nature lovers, and those interested in cultural experiences. With a ticket price of 15,000 Won, it offers a super worthwhile experience, as one reviewer put it. The park is well-maintained and can be covered in 90 minutes, making it accessible for visitors of all ages. The two caves, in particular, are highly praised for their beauty and well-maintained condition. Additionally, the park features a vast garden with cacti species, bonsai, and a traditional folk house set up, which can be a great alternative to visiting a separate folk village. The park is also known for its beautiful hydrangeas, bougainvilleas, and wooded trees, making it a paradise for garden enthusiasts. While some reviewers have noted that the animal enclosures could be improved, the overall experience of Hallim Park is highly recommended.
destinations.Name: Hallim Park

destinations.Address: 112-3 Sage-ri, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description:
Yongmeori Coast, a 4.4/5-rated tourist attraction in Jeju Island, is a must-visit natural landmark for nature lovers and adventure seekers. Located in Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo, this rocky coastline boasts unique cliff formations and breathtaking ocean views. Visitors can expect to enjoy scenic walks along the shore, with the added thrill of exploring the area's geological wonders.

The attraction is particularly popular during low tide, as it offers access to the coastal walk around the cliffs. However, it's essential to check the Jeju meteorology website before visiting, as the coastal walk may be closed due to high swells and strong winds. Despite these occasional closures, visitors can still appreciate the stunning views and atmospheric surroundings.

Yongmeori Coast is ideal for families, couples, and photography enthusiasts, as it offers a picturesque backdrop for memorable photos. The attraction's proximity to other popular landmarks in Jeju Island makes it a convenient stop for tourists exploring the region.

One of the special features of Yongmeori Coast is the Lava Tube, a massive volcanic formation that adds to the area's unique charm. Visitors can explore the layers of volcanic rocks, which were formed under the sea about 1.8 million years ago, and marvel at the mysterious scenery along the trails.

Overall, Yongmeori Coast offers a captivating experience for those seeking a blend of natural beauty, adventure, and cultural significance. Its unique geological formations, stunning views, and convenient location make it a must-visit attraction in Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Yongmeori Coast

destinations.Address: 347 Hwasunseodong-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Soingook Theme Park is a unique attraction in Jeju Island that offers visitors a chance to explore miniature replicas of famous landmarks from around the world. Located at 347 Hwasunseodong-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, this leafy garden is ideal for families, history enthusiasts, and nature lovers. Visitors can expect to see scaled-down versions of iconic structures such as cathedrals and palaces, with information provided in English. The park also features an amazing cafe, convenience store, Korean buffet restaurant, and a souvenir shop. With a 3.9/5 overall rating, visitors have praised the park for its easy location, variety of options, and well-maintained facilities. However, some reviews mention that the address on Google Maps is not accurate and that the park has been relocated. The admission ticket costs 7000 won per person, and the park is open for all age groups.
destinations.Name: Soingook Theme Park

destinations.Address: 956-6 Cheongsu-ri, Hangyeong-myeon, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Sanyang Keunkot Photo Spot is a picturesque attraction located in Hangyeong-myeon, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea. With an overall rating of 4.4/5, this natural landmark offers visitors a refreshing escape from the heat with its cool and quiet forest trails. The park is ideal for families, nature lovers, and photography enthusiasts, as it features a variety of scenic spots and photo opportunities. Visitors can expect to see beautiful and mystical sculptures, as well as a Snow White-themed Ecopark. While some reviewers found the entrance fee of approximately $5 to be somewhat expensive, many enjoyed the fresh air and the chance to take memorable photos. The park is easily accessible and located near other popular attractions in Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Sanyang Keunkot Photo Spot

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 도두동 산1
destinations.Description: Dodubong Peak, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated natural landmark with a 4.5/5 overall rating. Visitors can expect a short and safe climb to the peak, offering stunning 360-degree views of Jeju City, the sea, and Hallasan. The peak is particularly popular for plane spotting at Jeju Airport. Nature lovers and families will find this attraction ideal, as it offers a peaceful and scenic experience. The location is easily accessible and not crowded, making it a perfect spot for a leisurely hike. Visitors also appreciate the early cherry blossom bloomer surrounded by budding trees, adding to the attraction's natural beauty.
destinations.Name: Dodubong Peak

destinations.Description:
The Jeju Folklore and Natural History Museum is a must-visit attraction for those interested in the cultural traditions and natural history of Jeju Island. Located at 40 Samseong-ro, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea, this museum boasts a 4.2/5 overall rating and offers four exhibition halls filled with artifacts and models that trace the island's rich history. Visitors can expect to learn about the geographical, cultural, floral, and faunal aspects of Jeju, making it an ideal spot for history enthusiasts and nature lovers alike.

The museum's amenities are top-notch, with wheelchair accessibility throughout, a small gift shop, and vending machines. The entry fee is 2000 KRW for adults, and the ticket counter is located at the entrance via the main road. Visitor reviews highlight the museum's informative exhibits, which provide a comprehensive understanding of Jeju's history and culture. Some reviews also mention the availability of luggage storage and the variety of foreign visitors, making it a truly international experience.

In addition to the main exhibition hall, the museum features a rock exhibit outdoors and a section dedicated to history, geography, and marine life. The museum is a great place to visit during typhoon season or for those who prefer indoor attractions. Overall, the Jeju Folklore and Natural History Museum offers a memorable experience for anyone looking to learn more about the unique culture and natural history of Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Jeju Folklore and Natural History Museum

destinations.Address: 15 Yongduam-gil, 용담2동 Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description:
Yongduam Rock, a captivating oceanfront volcanic rock formation in Jeju Island, is a must-visit attraction for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts. Located at 15 Yongduam-gil, 용담2동 Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea, this natural landmark boasts a unique shape that resembles a dragon's head, making it an iconic symbol of the island. With an overall rating of 3.9/5, visitors can expect a memorable experience, as highlighted in the reviews.

One of the most appealing aspects of Yongduam Rock is its proximity to the sea, offering stunning views and a serene atmosphere. Visitors can park nearby and take a short walk to the rock formation, where they can appreciate its unique shape and the surrounding landscape. The area is also known for its local seafood vendors, providing a chance for tourists to enjoy fresh seafood right by the rock.

While some visitors may find the experience quick and straightforward, others appreciate the easy accessibility and the opportunity to witness the rare shape of the rocks along the beach. The attraction is ideal for families, couples, and adventure seekers looking for a quick stop during their Jeju Island exploration.

In addition to its natural beauty, Yongduam Rock offers a few stairways for those who want to get a closer look at the rock formation. The area is also popular for its views of the sea and the nearby Ramada hotel. For photography enthusiasts, the spot offers a unique vantage point to capture the landing trajectory of airplanes over the sea every two minutes.

Overall, Yongduam Rock is a must-visit attraction in Jeju Island, offering a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural experiences, and scenic views. Its convenient location and accessibility make it a perfect addition to any travel itinerary, and the visitor reviews highlight the attraction's ability to create memorable experiences for all who visit.
destinations.Name: Yongduam Rock
